"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"Creating an onion website is private, free, and can be deployed easier than a traditional domain. You'll save time and money by not going through the process of purchasing a domain and add-ons (like domain privacy), properly configuring your web hosting, and [providing personal and financial data to yet another vulnerable company](https://www.forbes.com/sites/daveywinder/2020/05/05/godaddy-confirms-data-breach-what-19-million-customers-need-to-know/?sh=18daecae1daa).\\n\\n### Step 1: Raspberry Pi Setup\\n\\nFirst, you should have an operational Raspberry Pi running a Debian-based OS. I used Raspbian via the [Raspberry Pi Imager](https://www.raspberrypi.com/software/).\\n\\n![Raspberry Pi Imager](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/s3g4KROXvHTmbKYOI_JwE.png?height=450&width=682)\\n\\n### Step 2: Nginx\\n\\nInstall Nginx [using this guide](https://pimylifeup.com/raspberry-pi-nginx/).\\n\\n![Command-line interface with the install command entered](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/35Gt77pxY7vjNKXb4A62R.png?height=373&width=572)\\n\\n### Step 3: Install Tor\\n\\n`sudo apt install -y tor`\\n\\n![Command-line interface installing Tor](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/GfyTvr5psnU3OwA0tdeWA.png?height=373&width=572)\\n\\n### Step 4: Create an Onion Service\\n\\nGo to your torrc file:\\n\\n`sudo nano /etc/tor/torrc`\\n\\nCreate an onion service by uncommenting these lines:\\n\\n`HiddenServiceDir /var/lib/tor/hidden_service/`\\n`HiddenServicePort 80 127.0.0.1:80`\\n\\n![Editing the torrc file](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/qQvzXsgZA5ggeCozhuL8K.png?height=345&width=572)\\n\\n### Step 5: Restart Tor\\n\\n`sudo systemctl restart tor`\\n\\n### Step 6: Find Your Onion Address\\n\\n`sudo nano /var/lib/tor/hidden_service/hostname`\\n\\n![Onion address displayed in the hostname file](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/OTfTZnnnqkGYS2IIzwMq4.png?height=345&width=572)\\n\\n### Step 7: Port Forwarding\\n\\nEnable port forwarding on your router for the Pi's local IP address and the port specified in your Torrc file.\\n\\n### Step 8: Visit your website!\\n\\nEnter your onion address in Tor Browser.\\n\\n![An onion website with the default nginx landing page](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/HRsCkbuujdL5nonKkeeJ6.png?height=787&width=952)\\n\\n### Next Steps\\n\\nüéâ Congratulations, you created an onion website! If you want to go further, check out the additional resources below:\\n\\n‚úÖ Install Raspian\\n\\n‚úÖ Install Nginx\\n\\n‚úÖ Install & Configure Tor\\n\\n‚úÖ Enable Port Forwarding\\n\\n‚¨úÔ∏è [Enable two-factor authentication](https://www.raspberrypi.com/news/setting-up-two-factor-authentication-on-your-raspberry-pi/) for SSH logins to your Pi\\n\\n‚¨úÔ∏è Read: [Best practices for hosting onion services](https://riseup.net/en/security/network-security/tor/onionservices-best-practices) from RiseUp\\n\\n‚¨úÔ∏è Read: [Setting up an onion service](https://community.torproject.org/onion-services/setup/) by The Tor Project\\n\\n‚¨úÔ∏è Read: [Take These Steps to Secure Your Raspberry Pi Against Attackers](https://makezine.com/2017/09/07/secure-your-raspberry-pi-against-attackers/) by Make Magazine\",\"timestamp\":1637604736,\"title\":\"Host your own onion website\"},\"digest\":\"zZI_JdP76nYSqL8__1dCbmjNLiZJ_Nnff317EUILYCQ\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xf4A3BBB8560D149C116d67CA5917A186cc13Fe30\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"vWlImahoGYV67vw7XX_VucRpo5RT47X35ofZ0thFCEs\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"rw6eBnmJo5znIw_IhL7GMo3KW4ULPM4BecOGXXtq2_c\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"9B5rC7o_IUfTfI3xE0guf-Wc4Ibri_cBoqZdGzlXPF0mcaGVhjJBtPMukZTKpgO7bvmO2Uaa6d71jdL-Oq3EiQ\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xebdc05550e7fcc4910ea495855552fb90e42e319474dac78eeabda8b839883d72249ec17e6a81fe9096b5ed26a6d828d52726f905d2d8df424f2846c454a63351c\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"vWlImahoGYV67vw7XX_VucRpo5RT47X35ofZ0thFCEs\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"rw6eBnmJo5znIw_IhL7GMo3KW4ULPM4BecOGXXtq2_c\\\"}\",\"algorithm\":{\"name\":\"ECDSA\",\"hash\":\"SHA-256\"}},\"nft\":{},\"version\":\"12-21-2020\",\"originalDigest\":\"fMNlFVnZpic68GRnHXRcq2hoYit0IcD1C-l-mSv5pEU\"}"